cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.SE, cs.DC

This paper focuses on the security of networked embedded devices, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper specifically addresses the use of honeypots for improving IoT security, which is a subfield of network security (cs.NI). The proposed architecture also involves distributed systems and scalability, which are topics in systems and control (cs.SY) and software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the use of wormholes to connect physically located devices to the Internet involves networking and distributed computing (cs.DC).
